{
  "texts": [
    "Imagine a uniform grid imposed on the hypercube, creating a lattice of smaller cubes.",
    "This division scheme ensures a finer analysis of the point distribution as the dimensionality increases.",
    "Each subcube is assigned a weight based on the number of points that fall within its boundaries.",
    "Subcubes containing more points receive a higher weight, reflecting a denser point concentration.",
    "The L 2 -star discrepancy is a normalized measure that captures the deviation between the ideal weight distribution (equal weight for all subcubes) and the actual weight distribution across the subcubes."
  ]
}